Module 1: Basics of AI Coding

How does programming give you an edge? 
- Automate repetitive tasks
- Analyse lot of data
- Build, improve and use AI models 

Python is everywhere in AI
- Self driving cars
- Chatbots
- Smart agriculture
- Financial services etc

First code - 
print ("Hello World!")

Types of data in computer programming
- text
- image
- audio
- tabular data

Strings are used to store and manipulate text. Strings are written inside of quotes and can contain letters, numbers, punctuation marks, and other special characters

If you use triple quotation marks, you can store a multiline string. These strings can span more than one line.

Integers and Floats
Integers represent numbers with no decimal part
Floats have digits after the decimal place 

In computer programming, variables are used to store, process, and manipulate data.
What are variables for? 
- Give a value a name to use later 
- Use the same name to refer to changing values 


